        <c02 level="item" id="d1e192">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Samuel Woodworth</persname>to Mr.
                  Bradish</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">[1829 Mar]</unitdate>
            <physdesc>ANS, 1 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Invites him to dinner.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e206">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Samuel Woodworth</persname>to 
                  <persname>Benjamin F. Thompson</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1837 Nov 25</unitdate>
            <physdesc>ALS, 3 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Discusses the celebration of a recent Whig
                  victory; reports that theatrical benefits on his
                  behalf at the 
                  <corpname>National Theater</corpname>and the 
                  <corpname>Bowery</corpname>netted him more than three
                  thousand dollars; discusses his son's visit to 
                  <geogname>Hempstead</geogname>and the poor state of
                  his health; asks Thompson to give his regard to
                  family friends.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e231">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Samuel Woodworth</persname>to 
                  <persname>Benjamin F. Thompson</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1838 Jan 4</unitdate>
            <physdesc>ALS, 2 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Gives New Year's greetings; describes his vision
                  of the Virgin Mary and its influence on a letter he
                  was writing; believes he is blessed to have a happy
                  marriage and family; argues that a couple who really
                  love each other will be reunited in the spiritual
                  world; looks forward to the afterlife.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e247">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Nelson F. Adkins</persname>to Captain
                  Pleadwell</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1945 Mar 26</unitdate>
            <physdesc>ALS, 3 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Discusses the contents of a Woodworth letter;
                  believes a quotation might be from Byron or Moore;
                  agrees that Woodworth might have referred to 
                  <persname>Emanuel Swedenborg</persname>'s 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Delights of Wisdom Pertaining to
                     Conjugal Love</title></bibref>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
      </c01>
